  "prompt": "Where can I get free singing lessons via Skype?",
  "response": "Finding free singing lessons via Skype can be challenging, but there are several resources and platforms that might offer what you're looking for:\n\n1. **YouTube**: Many vocal coaches offer free tutorials and lessons on their YouTube channels. While these might not be live or interactive, they can provide valuable information and exercises.\n\n2. **Facebook Groups**: There are various groups dedicated to singing and vocal training where members sometimes offer free lessons or tips. You can search for relevant groups and join them.\n\n3. **Reddit**: The subreddit r/singing often has users offering free advice and sometimes free lessons. You can browse the posts or make a request for free Skype lessons.\n\n4. **Online Forums**: Websites like VoiceCouncil or The Modern Vocalist often have forums where members might offer free lessons or practice sessions.\n\n5. **Local Music Schools or Non-profits**: Some local music schools or non-profit organizations might offer free lessons or have volunteer opportunities where you can get free training.\n\n6. **Skillshare and Coursera**: Occasionally, these platforms offer free trials or courses that include singing lessons. They might not be on Skype, but they can still be very helpful.\n\nIt's important to be cautious and ensure the person offering free lessons is credible and experienced. You can check reviews or ask for references to verify their qualifications.",
